 IV — and won. He went on to win the King's Cup, Astor Cup, and Puritan Cup in 1939, the three most coveted domestic yachting trophies in a single season — a feat considered without parallel. He was posthumously inducted into the America's Cup Hall of Fame in 1993.","number":2},{"header":"He led the 1939 Boston Committee to save","body":"In September 1939, Charles Francis Adams III headed the 'Boston Committee' — a group including FDR's uncle Frederick Delano and Harold Vanderbilt — formed to save the Charles W. Morgan, the last surviving American whaling ship, for New Bedford. His involvement helped convince the Old Dartmouth Historical Society to lead the rescue campaign.","number":3}],"bio":{"display_name":"Charles Francis Adams III","first_name":"Charles","last_name":"Adams","married_names":[],"middle_name":"Francis","suffix":"III","nickname":"Deacon"},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[{"institution_id":"INST002"}],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"charles-adams-iii-1866"},"X02099":{"id":"X02099","is_placeholder":false,"gender":"female","has_descendants_documented":true,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":false,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"birth":{"year":1869,"month":1,"day":16,"city":"Taunton","county":"Bristol County","state":"Massachusetts"},"death":{"year":1956,"month":4,"day":8},"parents":{"father_research_notes":"William C. Lovering, U.S. Representative from Massachusetts"},"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"X02098","children_ids":["X01632"],"date_year":1899,"date_month":4,"date_day":3}],"number_of_marriages":1,"tags":[],"sources":[{"short":"FindAGrave"}],"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"cross_connections":[],"bio":{"display_name":"Frances Lovering Adams","first_name